"""Adaptor Roundup

A container adaptor does not implement its own storage or its own algorithms -- it wraps an existing container (usually std::deque) and exposes a narrower, purpose-built interface on top of it. std::stack, std::queue, and std::priority_queue are the three standard adaptors. This activity is a round of scenario trials: for each workload, decide which adaptor fits (or whether the honest answer is 'none of them -- use a plain std::vector'), and why.
"""
